{{History of the United States}}
This is a [[bibliography]] of works on the [[military history of the United States]]. <center>{{Expand list|date=September 2011}}</center>
==Surveys== {{refbegin}} * Allison, William T. [[Jeffrey Grey|Jeffrey G. Grey]], Janet G. Valentine. ''American Military History: A Survey from Colonial Times to the Present'' (2nd ed. 2012) 416pp *{{cite book |author=Crocker H. W., III|title=Don't Tread on Me: A 400-Year History of America at War|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EHI-RHlEv_wC&pg=PP1|year=2007|publisher=Random House Digital, Inc.|isbn=978-1-4000-5364-3}} *{{cite book |editor=Chambers, John Whiteclay |editor2=Fred Anderson |title=The Oxford companion to American military history|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_Rzy_yNMKbcC&pg=PP1|year=1999|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-507198-6}} *{{cite book |author=Lookingbill, Brad D. |title=American Military History|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rxVFCFnPKOEC&pg=PP1|date=19 October 2010|publisher=John Wiley and Sons|isbn=978-1-4051-9052-7}} * Anderson, Fred, ed. ''The Oxford Companion to American Military History'' (2000) *{{cite book |authors=Army, U. S. Department of the|title=The Writing of American Military History: A Guide|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BIlTnoCVy_YC&pg=PP1|date=1 June 2001|publisher=The Minerva Group, Inc.|isbn=978-0-89875-350-9}} * Black, Jeremy. ''Fighting for America: The Struggle for Mastery in North America, 1519-1871'' (2011) * Boyne, Walter J. ''Beyond the Wild Blue: A History of the U.S. Air Force, 1947–2007'' (2007) [http://www.amazon.com/dp/0312358113/ excerpt and text search], popular * Chambers, ed. John Whiteclay. ''The Oxford Guide to American Military History'' (1999) ISBN 0-19-507198-0 * Futrell, Robert Frank. ''Ideas, Concepts, Doctrine: A History of Basic Thinking in the United States Air Force'' (2 vol. 1979) * Doughty, Robert. ''American Military History and the Evolution of Western Warfare'', (1996) ISBN 0-669-41683-5 *{{cite book |author1=Hacker, Barton C. |author2=Margaret Vining|title=American Military Technology: The Life Story of a Technology|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=a3KLJN5kigQC&pg=PP1|date=November 2007|publisher=JHU Press|isbn=978-0-8018-8772-7}} * Hearn, Chester G. ''Air Force: An Illustrated History: The U.S. Air Force from 1910 to the 21st Century'' (2008), popular [http://www.amazon.com/dp/0760333084/ excerpt and text search] * Howarth, Stephen. ''To Shining Sea: A History of the United States Navy, 1775–1998'' (1999) [http://www.amazon.com/dp/0806130261/ excerpt and text search]; a standard history * Huston, James A. ''The Sinews of War: Army Logistics, 1775-1953'' (1966), U.S. Army; 755pp [https://books.google.com/books?id=Y8pabWzrsocC ] * Love, Robert W. '' History of the U.S. Navy, 1775–1941'' (1992) and ''History of the U.S. Navy, 1942–1991'' (1992) [http://www.amazon.com/dp/081171862X/ vol 1 excerpt and text search]; [http://www.amazon.com/dp/0811718638/ vol 2 excerpt and text search]; a standard history * Matloff, Maurice, ed. ''American Military History'' (1996) [http://www.history.army.mil/books/AMH/amh-toc.htm full text online]; standard textbook used in ROTC; Now replaced by Richard Stewart 2010 * Millett, Allan R., and Peter Maslowski, and William B. Feis. ''For the common defense: a military history of the United States of America'' (3rd ed. 2013) * Millett, Allan R. ''Semper Fidelis. A History of the United States Marine Corps'' (1991) * {{cite book|author=Moten, Matthew|title=Presidents and Their Generals: An American History of Command in War|url=http://www.amazon.com/Presidents-Their-Generals-American-History-ebook/dp/B00OVWIWGW/|year=2014|publisher=Harvard UP}} * Muehlbauer, Matthew S., and David J. Ulbrich. ''Ways of War: American Military History from the Colonial Era to the Twenty-First Century'' (Routledge, 2013), 536pp; university textbook; [http://www.miwsr.com/2014-105.aspx online review] * Stewart, Richard W. ''American military history'' (2 vol 2010) *{{cite book |author1=Sweeney, Jerry K. |author2=Kevin B. Byrne|title=A handbook of American military history|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4-_WwWMkBRQC|date=1 May 2006|publisher=U of Nebraska Press|isbn=978-0-8032-9337-3}} *{{cite book |author=Urwin, Gregory J. W. |title=The United States Cavalry: an illustrated history, 1776-1944|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fZoaSDGQXLUC&pg=PP1|year=1983|publisher=University of Oklahoma Press|isbn=978-0-8061-3475-8}} * Weigley, Russell Frank. ''History of the United States army'' (1967) * Weigley, Russell Frank. ''The American Way of War: A History of United States Military Strategy and Policy'', (1977) [http://www.amazon.com/dp/025328029X/ excerpt and text search] *{{cite book |author=Williams, T. Harry|title=Americans at War: The Development of the American Military System|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=747u1NJAtdYC&pg=PP1|year=1960|publisher=LSU Press|isbn=978-0-8071-2474-1}}
===Historiography=== * Grimsley, Mark. "The American military history master narrative: Three textbooks on the American military experience," ''Journal of Military History'' (2015) 79#3 pp 782-802; review of Allison, Millett, and Muehlbauer textbooks
